message.content:
A West Highland White Terrier is a small, sturdy dog breed originating from Scotland. 
They are typically around 10-11 inches tall and weigh between 15-22 pounds. 
Their coat is thick and white, with a wiry texture. 
Their ears stand erect and their tail is medium length and carried high. 
They have a distinctive round face with dark, almond-shaped eyes and a black nose. 
These dogs are known for their friendly and lively personality, and are often used as companion pets. 
They can also be found participating in various dog sports and activities such as obedience trials and agility competitions.
